item.title: Ares Warsword, Shield, and Chestplate[Released].blend/.3ds
item.dc:creator: @Cole1497 Cole1497
item.description:
@Cole1497 wrote:

[quote=“reyx7, post:92, topic:396065”][quote author=Cole1497 link=topic=493245.msg3906907#msg3906907 date=1328323596]

You don’t mind if I mod these into Oblivion, do you?

By all means, use it for whatever you would like. Though I would recommend removing some poly on the handle of the sword, as it wasn’t made as a lowpoly handle. All I ever ask for is credit when necessary.

If I plan to release the Oblivion mod I’ll definitely credit you.

How many people still play Oblivion? I stopped playing it once I started making spells that could drop 20 people instantly. It took awhile to get to that point, but it was great when it finally happened.

I lost my original account so I’ve started over. Plus, I’ve been using quite a few more mods to enhance gameplay. It’s still a very fun game.
[/quote]
Skyrim modding has now officially became “easy” (you know, not so down to earth), so if you’re looking to be up to date, see [url=http://www.moparisthebest.com/smf/index.php/topic,534323.0.html[/url]here.[/quote]
I don’t doubt it’s easier, I’ve heard about the TES V Construction kit, but that’s not what I was talking about.
(although, if someone wants to rip the daedric armor/textures from Skyrim I’ll gladly take them.)

Read full topic

item.dc:creator: @dylan_0789 dylan_0789
item.description:
@dylan_0789 wrote:

[quote=“Cole1497, post:73, topic:396065”]Dylan, you should really start using uppit. I’ve tried downloading some of your older models, and they’re no longer available.

But thank you for the Ares set.[/quote]
In all honesty, most of those past models are gone. Since their release I have gotten a new computer. The links died because the files had been innactive for so long. I might re make some of the models, such as my Godsword Concept/Masamune, which I think were my two most downloaded. To those who are looking for my Masamune model: You can most likely find it on older Delta clients.

Ares set is incomplete, I do apologize, as the shield and chestplate are not really ‘complete.’ This is an unfinished project, but as I am not finishing it, I figured I would release what I had.
